line_1: Ergo the whole Dispute is ended.
line_2: You grant, at least, She is extended:

line_1: Thus the Dispute is wisely ended.
line_2: What from her Tale He comprehended:

line_1: Eat now, and weep when dinner's ended,
line_2: Let not thy stomach be suspended,

line_1: Nor yet when even tide was ended,
line_2: Nor yet at eve his note suspended,

line_1: He saw her days were near hand ended,
line_2: But, waes my heart! he could na mend it

line_1: Reply'd; Brave Sir, your Time is ended,

line_2: Bad luck can ne'er be mended;

line_1: And your last volume's nearly ended,
line_2: At length when every woe's expended,

line_1: No more I'll insist, lest your patience be ended;
line_2: I beg by my scrawl, sir, you'll not be offended;
